               <p>WILLIAM WRIGHT. I am a <rs id="t18261026-222-viclabel1223" type="occupation">confectioner</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261026-222-victim1308 t18261026-222-viclabel1223"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261026-222-victim1309 t18261026-222-viclabel1223"></join>, in partnership with my father, Cornelius Wright. The prisoner was <rs id="t18261026-222-deflabel1224" type="occupation">employed to make biscuits</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261026-222-defend1307 t18261026-222-deflabel1224"></join>. On the evening of the 27th of September, the errand-boy called me from tea - I came down, and sent a man after the prisoner, who brought him back and Coombs took this sugar from him - he said he was going to take it home; I found 2lbs. of sugar in his hat, and the butter in a bag.</p>
